Community-acquired pneumonia due to Bordetella holmesii in a patient with frequently relapsing nephrotic syndrome. Bordetella holmesii is a rare cause of human infection, mainly in the immunocompromised host, and is associated with bacteremia, respiratory tract infection and endocarditis. Herein, we describe a patient with severe relapse of nephrotic syndrome associated with bacteremic B. holmesii pneumonia.